Description: Network Emulator Equipment Vendor
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Giganet Systems develops and manufactures network emulators for the Test & Measurement industry. For obvious reasons, companies cannot, or will not, introduce an untested product or service into a live network. The old solution involved plenty of cable strung between devices to try and replicate a network. Unfortunately, this provides neither realistic, or repeatable, results.  As their name implies, network emulators re-create real-world network conditions such as latency, loss, re-order, jitter and much more and allow for the validation of a company's  products and services against real-world network conditions.  Once tested against a network emulator from Giganet Systems, Enterprises, Service Providers and Network Equipment Manufacturers will know exactly how their product or service will perform when deployed.

That is why Julie Foudy, Women's World Cup co-captain has joined our company as an advisor and spokeswoman, and why Dick Schaap, noted sports journalist and longtime Women's Sports Foundation supporter has joined our Board of Directors. We are all part of Team TFA, here to serve you, the female athlete, and your mom, dad, and coach. When you join Team TFA, at our website, you discover not only the best products but also the most up-to-date information on female athletics. You also get a forum to tell us what you think about current teams, sports topics, and products.

Description: Where Urban Living Thrives
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: HalfCity is the most elegant urban life sharing social platform that targets the Chinese market, launching by end of Dec. 2012. Half City is your one-stop information show-room that displays all facets about a city from the urban dwellers’ point of view, brings you the most authentic AND graceful urban life sharing experience.  What to have for lunch? Where to hangout on weekends? What’s in trend in Shanghai? While you may think all this information can be found on either Da Zhong Dian Ping(Chinese version of Yelp) or Weibo(Chinese version of Twitter), there is no one platform that aggregates these fragments with a single city theme and easy-to-use photo template that highlights the user’s mood and location all at once.  The Spirit: The majority of us live in an urban environment. HalfCity was hoping to build a platform that captures the urban spirit, which to most of us is highly fragmented and dynamic, for city dwellers to share their lives with their folks.  Half City also wanted to add a graceful touch to that as the team believe in a calm and peaceful attitude toward life.  Half City enriches users’ urban living experience by revealing a city’s beauty from all those who live or have lived there, thus creating the most colorful and interesting Urban Life guide.

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: SnapLayout is a [MySpace](http://crunchbase.com/organization/myspace) profile editor from the [Y Combinator](http://crunchbase.com/organization/y-combinator) company [Weebly](http://crunchbase.com/organization/weebly).  Tired of a lack of innovation from MySpace's end, the Weebly guys created a simple profile editor to help the millions of users looking to better customize their personal page. The SnapLayout editor is pretty easy to use.  MySpace users log in to SnapLayout with their MySpace credentials and use a "what you see is what you get" (WYSIWYG) editor to rearrange the major features of their page.  Users can use an array of SnapLayout's templates or drag and drop sections of their page wherever they'd like.   [Flickr](http://crunchbase.com/organization/flickr) photos can be used as backdrops, text size, style and color can be changed.  SnapLayout even lets you place your uploaded photos in a slide show.  It also has a widget platform which will include apps created by the company.  The first is a virtual gift widget which mimics the very popular [Facebook](http://crunchbase.com/organization/facebook) feature. SnapLayout offers an addition to Myspace that will be popular with its users.  We'll see how MySpace reacts if SnapLayout gains traction.

We are the Geeks. The Nerds. The high-waist, tape on glass, high-pitch people that you see in TV. We're not famous but we're good at what we do and love it death. The fact that you are reading this...is surprising. You probably got directed to our site because of our review on a product, our insight on a particular technology-category, or just because you're searching the web and have nothing better to do. The address is...sike, we don't post that since the founder of this business is a college student in Southfield, Michigan.
